SINGAPORE DAYBOOK: Singapore Airlines, Matex, TTJ Holdings

-- B y   J a n   D a h i n t e n   a n d   P h o e b e   S e d g m a n
-- 
2011-03-09T22:17:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/singapore-daybook-singapore-airlines-matex-ttj-holdings.html
  Singapore  Airlines Ltd., the
world’s second-biggest carrier by market value, said it will
raise its fuel surcharge by between $2 and $26 per ticket from
March 17 to offset rising jet fuel prices.  MARKETS:  *The MSCI Asia Pacific Index rose 0.3 percent at yesterday’s
close.
*Singapore’s Straits Times Index shed 0.4 percent at yesterday’s
close.
*The  Dow Jones Industrial Average  retreated 0.01 percent at
yesterday’s close.
*The Stoxx Europe 600 Index declined 0.2 percent at yesterday’s
close.  EQUITY MOVERS:  *CapitaLand Ltd. (CAPL SP):  Southeast Asia ’s biggest developer
said its Indian units will acquire four joint-ventures for
S$38.5 million.
*Matex International Ltd. (MTEX SP): The supplier of chemicals
used in the  textile industry  said its full-year loss widened to
3.2 Singapore cents per share from the 2.85 Singapore cents per
share loss announced on Feb. 26 after it booked an impairment
charge on its trade receivables.
*Singapore Airlines Ltd. (SIA SP): The world’s second-biggest
carrier by market value said it will increase its fuel surcharge
by between $2 and $26 per ticket from March 17 to offset rising
jet fuel prices.
*Stamford Tyres Corp. (STC SP): The Singapore-based retailer and
distributor of tires said third-quarter net income increased 26
percent to S$2.9 million from a year ago.
*TTJ Holdings Ltd. (TTJ SP): The Singapore-based supplier of
structural steel said first-half net income doubled to S$4.7
million from S$2.3 million.  BTV Guests:  7:10 a.m.: Former Australian Ambassador Bob Bowker
7:40 a.m.: Cathay Pacific Chief Operating Officer John Slosar
7:50 a.m.: Westpac Senior Economist Dominick Stephens
8:40 a.m.: Association of Asia-Pacific Airlines Director-General
Andrew Herdman
9:00 a.m.: HSBC Asia Economist Song Yi Kim
10:10 a.m.: Nomura Deputy Head of Asian Economy Tomo Kinoshita
10:40 a.m.: Lloyd’s of London CEO Richard Ward
2:00 p.m.: East West Bank Chairman & CEO Dominic Ng  To contact the reporter on this story:
